                            <comment id="14708124" author="tsuresh" created="Sat, 22 Aug 2015 18:29:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Scanning through the code I found out  there is org.apache.spark.sql.jdbcDialects  class that  nicely defines interface to handles data type differences in different databases and already has implementation for MySQL, and Postgres. Following the same approach, I added a DB2 dialect that maps String Type to CLOB, it fixed the issue I ran into.   I am working on submitting the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
